{ Trying to avoid the queen exchange:   14...Qe3+  15.Qxe3  Nxe3  16.Bb5+  . Here a neat finish might be:  16...Ke7  17.Rfe1!  Nxc2  18.d6+!  cxd6  or   18...Kxd6  19.Rad1+  19.Nd5+  Kf8  20.e7+  Kg7  21.e8=Q  Rxe8  22.Rxe8  Nxa1  23.Ne7  . White picks up a whole piece. }
15. Ne4
{ By no means the only good move, but the Danish GM wants to exploit his central majority to the maximum. }
15... Qe3+ 16. Qxe3 Nxe3 17. d6 { Olé! } 17... Nxc4
{ 17...Nxf1  18.Nxf6+  Kf8  or   18...Kd8  19.e7  19.Rxf1  would also be quite hopeless:  19...Kg7  20.Nh5+  Kg6  21.Rf7  Kxh5  22.Rg7!  . White is forcing mate. }
