{ Only now do we check and again leave Black with a position where his most natural move isn't the best. }
11... Be6
{ By a ratio of about three to one, Black's most popular choice, but now White has a strong rook lift. }
12. Re4
{ Reminding Black that his advanced pawns can very much be a target and are not just a strength. }
12... d3 { A critical test as Black maintains his central pawn. } 13. Nbd2
{ Not the only good square for the knight  13.Nc3  Rxg7  14.Re3  is a decent alternative, but one which carries a threat and is fairly easy for White to play. }
