{ Once described by the experienced Hungarian Grandmaster Peter Lukacs as 'very ugly', we rather like this bold advance, and not just because it makes good use of Harry!  It should also catch out plenty of opponents, not least followers of the generally excellent course 'Lifetime Repertoires: Jan Gustafsson's  1.e4  e5' or Martin Lokander's 'Open Games with Black' repertoire book.  Naturally White must avoid  11.Nxd4??  Qxh2+  @@StartBracket@@  11.Bf6?!  also rather backfires in view of  11...Bxh2+!  @@EndBracket@@, while plenty of praxis has shown that Black is OK after  11.Nxd6+  cxd6  12.Bf4  Qd5!  , and if  13.c3  O-O  , returning the pawn to reach a rather sterile position - something which is not the case after the text move. }
