{ This further pawn sacrifices continues to ask some questions of Black and aim for more than  16.Nxd4  Nxd4  17.Qxd4  would do. }
16... Qxc4
{ Critical, but Black should probably prefer  16...Qc5  . Will you be the first to test this unbalanced position, where  17.Nd2  and  17.b4!?  are two ideas,  17.Rb1!?  another, and if  Kb8  18.b4!  Qxc4  19.b5  Ne7  20.Nxd4  , thereby retaining sufficient pressure and activity for the pawn with  Nxe6  the immediate threat. }
