{ By no means forced, but the most critical move. White's activity and bishop-pair supply full compensation, as they certainly do after }
14... Bf6
{ Unsurprisingly Black can't snaffle a second pawn with   14...Bxh4??  because of  15.Be2  ,  and   14...Nxh4?!  15.Rh5  Rfe8   15...Ng6  16.Rxh7  Rad8  17.Kc2  followed by Bd3 and Bd4 does not look too appealing for Black  16.R1xh4  Bxh4  17.Rxh4  also looks rather attractive for White with two such fine bishops and very much the chance to target the black queenside as well as kingside. }
