{ Not the only way to recapture, but one that gives White options of Rb2 and even of Na3 followed by Qa1. }
10... Nf6 11. O-O Be7 12. Qe2
{ White still has only one pawn for the piece, but he is set to roll ahead with e5 and d4-d5, and must enjoy at least decent practical compensation, as shown by }
12... d6 13. d4 Bg4 14. Qe3
{ with much the better coordination and Nd2 followed by f4 high on the agenda, starting to launch the central juggernaut. }
