5. Nf3 { White wants to maintain the bridgehead on e5, not the g2-pawn. } 5...
Qxg2 6. Rg1 Qh3 7. d4
{ Clearly White has some compensation. There's a definite lead in development, a strong centre, a half-open g-file and an offside black queen to kick. The engines aren't initially completely sold on the gambit, pointing to a prophylactic defensive try: }
7... h6 8. c3
{ 8.Bf4  g5  9.Bg3  Ne7  left Black expanding with tempo in Trimitzios-A.Moskalenko, Internet @@StartBracket@@blitz@@EndBracket@@ 2020, although he still went on to lose. }
