{ However, even this doesn't seem so clear with Nf1-e3 and Bc2 on their way. One instructive line runs: }
9... Nf5 10. Nf1 c5 { Thematically trying to liberate Black's position. } 11.
dxc5 Bxc5 12. Be3 Nxe3 13. Nxe3 Bxe3 14. fxe3 g6 15. Qe2
{ White will castle long and enjoys a promising initiative with the e4 break high on the agenda. }
